rComments: All I could say is that she is amazing!!
Super kind.

Prof Critoph is a great! Her lectures are straightforward, you can tell she is really passionate about the topic. Gives great feedback on essays/quizzes, is a fair grader and overall wants students to do well. One of the better econ profs at UofO - highly recommend. Do you work, pay attention, ask questions and you'll do great!

Prof was super respectful and explained things very well. Always thanked students for asking questions and took the time to answer them thoughtfully. Tests and weekly assignments on Cengage were straightforward. Posted videos that cover the week's content but also does live lectures. Will be taking her again.
I like the structure of the class. She is very kind and cares about her students.

Absolutely love this prof! She's so sweet and accommodating. Every time someone has a question, she'd answer them patiently and would make the students feel comfortable with asking questions by saying "thanks for asking". Very good with explaining lecture contents and provides pre-recorded lessons in case you can't attend class synchronously.

I am not an Econ major but her classes were very easy to follow and enjoyable to learn about. She is very clear and takes the time to answer any questions. We did have to buy mindtap with aplia though which I would have preferred not to.
She is really nice and if you attend class, take notes, and do the assignments, you'll do fine on the exams and pass no problems.

As someone else has said, the course's reliance on neoclassical approaches & presenting one view as a hard science is very concerning. Explains the deeply engrained fallacies amongst the student pop. regarding government spending, the relationship between min wage + unemployment, etc. Prof was nice & easy A but didn't go outside the box.

She is really an excellent professor. She is not only beautiful, but also very conscientious and responsible. When students encounter problems, she can give quick answers and give solutions. I highly recommend her course.

She is nice and good-looking, making you want to go to class. She explains everything very well. Always available in the office hour and helping you out. Answering your email and everything. She even hold two office hours for us in the final exam period. If you wanna have a enjoyable class time and a good grade, just pick her class when u can
This professor is so caring. If you have a problem just email her, shes always so willing to help. Her class, is interesting and she explains every concept clearly. I strongly recommend this prof

Very nice prof, always seemed to care about her students. Her lectures were a bit boring but the content was still clear and easy to understand. I think we should have had more lecture time as the classes sometimes were a bit rushed. Overall great prof and very nice person.
Very nice. My favorite prof.

She was very warm welcoming I guess you could say, answers almost all your questions about upcoming midterms/finals and is very clear during lectures. I am a first year student and I was definitely pleased with the format of her teaching. Definitely manage your time well on her midterms though, not sure about final yet. Would take again if possible
Really clear grading criteria. Put in the work and you will succeed.
Honestly, one of the best econ profs I've had so far. I'd recommend doing the readings as well as practice assignments she puts up. She's really sweet!
she's great, an easy A!

really good at explaining course material and what will be on exams, prepares you really well and goes out of her way to help students! also cares about what she teaches and is excited to explain, best class this semester for sure and critoph is just so nice

Prof Critoph is such a gem! Very clear lectures with summary videos available on BS, attentive to students needs and questions, multiple choice exams but very clear and correspond to material covered in class. Class requires to buy $80ish access to online platform for assignments (another $150 for physical textbook) but actually helpful to review.
Her lectures are amazing and so is she. Highly Recommend for ECO 1102.

You have to buy the textbook and do weekly quizzes through the textbook but honestly, it keeps you up to date on your studies. Her midterms are very fair and so far I've got a 98 on the midterm. She even gives a practice midterm that's MC which is super helpful. This is the only class I feel safe in this sem.

Prof Critoph is the sweetest prof you can get! She goes through the most important topics of the textbook in class and answers questions helpfully. If you can, take this class with her: the exams are on what she goes through in her power points and the weekly cengage assignements are free marks!

Took a course with her when she was teaching at Carleton University. Material was interesting and she was well prepared. Lectures were a bit standard and dry. Allows for a good amount of freedom when doing assignments which is a big plus for a Masters' Degree program.

I wasn't expecting to like this course as much as I did. Prof. Critoph is incredibly kind and understanding. She does a really good job at explaining course concepts and answering questions. I also liked the mix of synchronous and synchronous classes.

The overreliance on multiple choice based on neoclassical foundations in introduction economics courses worries me. Elise Critoph is a great professor, though; she is great at condensing flows of thought re these economic models.

This class was relatively easy and I am not a student who typically does well in ECON/math-related subjects. I didn't watch the lectures all that much as I found connect to be super helpful. The assignments related to the content and mcgraw hill connect offered many practice Qs that were super helpful to study. Midterms and final were very fair.

This class is pretty easy and I got through it by mainly just using the textbook and skimming through the lectures. I think you will do well by taking textbook notes and doing the assignments and practice questions on Connect. The midterms and finals were extremely fair and easy as well.

She is a very kind and accessible prof. She is organized and was willing to help. However, the lectures in this class were not filmed by her, it was another teacher. The lectures were hard to understand and I relied mostly on the textbook to learn all the content and chapters. Lots of readings. Recommend to do the exercises. Tests can be hard too.
teacherRatingTags: ['Test heavy', 'Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: I literally would listen to her video lectures till the end just to hear her say "Ok... bye now". She was super sweet and would quickly respond to emails to answer your questions. Her assignments on McGraw connect weren't always easy but it was always related to her course content. Definitely a solid choice!!!
She's nice

I can understand teaching online might be harder for profs but it seems the prof didn't try to make it easier for us students. Very hard class, didn't understand any videos, had to teach myself with the book. Hour long videos staring at a blank screen with the most monotone voice ever. No effort to capt attention.

By far the worst teacher I've ever had. Does a horrible job at actually explaining topics, didn't go through a single concrete example the entire course, and is extremely unhelpful when asked questions. Her lecture time each week was about half what we should have- may seem like a good thing, but it means you'll be teaching yourself most things.

I loved the way this class was organized. Very clear and you know exactly what to do/study to prepare for the exams. Kinda messed up on one of my midterms and I emailed her about my mistake and she responded quickly and told me she'd take care of it (and she did). Really sweet and kind and wants to see her students succeed in the course.
teaches very clearly and in an organized manner. tests reflect lecture material. seems like a kind person :)

Very kind and sweet professor. With the coronavirus, online classes can be very confusing and disorganized. However, her class was very organized and I always knew what I had to do and where I could find information on how to do it. This made taking her class such a breath of fresh air. 10/10 would take her classes again.

Excellent prof. She is very sweet and super chill. Not a big fan of economics, but I was able to learn a lot more than I thought I would. She explains the material VERY WELL. Midterm can't be picked up, but she allows you to go over it as many times as you need, and will answer any question (PERFECT one-on-one explanations during office hours).

Bad class, even worse prof. Incredibly monotone and boring, seems like she was forced to teach. Writing on the board is not legible, assignments have nothing to do with the course content. I would do my assignments with my notes right in front of me and I still wasn't able to understand. Avoid this prof at all costs.
GREAT PROF!!!!!!!!!!! WOW!!!!!!
